Patch Set 1:

> Patch Set 1:
> 
> Ok so QtVSTools also depends on the Qt version used to compile VsQml. As far as I know, C# does not accept BLA=514 defines, but only booleans. So QtVSTools could have QT514 and QT515 but that would be something the user has to do manually. Can someone think of a more automatic way?
> 
> Perhaps in the long run we should have a copy of the AST stuff from declarative which is updated regularly like Creator does as far as I know.

Crazy idea: using T4 text templates, parse the AST header and extract only what is needed. We could use C# attribs to mark target types with a "path" to their C++ counterparts. Something like:

    [QmlAst(File="src/qml/parser/qqmljsast_p.h", Type="UiImport")]
    public class UiImport : AstNode
    {
        public UiImport() : base(AstNodeKind.UiImport) { }
        public SourceLocation FileNameToken { get; set; }
        [QmlAst.MaxVersion("5.13")]
        public SourceLocation VersionToken { get; set; }
        [QmlAst.MinVersion("5.14")]
        public UiVersionSpecifier Version { get; set; }
        public SourceLocation AsToken { get; set; }
        public SourceLocation ImportIdToken { get; set; }
    }

Also, by just fetching the fields that are actually used, we maximize the "future-proofness", vis-a-vis any further changes to the QML parser.

